      section#large-oper
        h2 Large Operators
        p.
          Below are the three most common #[i large operators] used in high school math:
          the limit, the integral, and the summation. The best explanation is by example.
          #[ins(datetime="2014-11-23") The first table shows Inline Mode and the second table shows Block Mode.]
        dl.o-FlexContainer.
          #[dt.u-w_p2c: code $$ \lim_{x \to -\infty} e^{x} $$]            #[dd.u-w_p2: span.M.M--B \lim_{x \to -\infty} e^{x}]
          #[dt.u-w_p2c: code $$ \int_{1}^{e} \frac{1}{x}\ dx $$]          #[dd.u-w_p2: span.M.M--B \int_{1}^{e} \dfrac{1}{x}\ dx]
