      section#conclusion
        h2 Conclusion
        p.
          That&rsquo;s it for now!
          #[a(href="mailto:chrisharvey2pi@gmail.com") Email me]
          if you have any questions or if you want me to add anything you think needs to be here.
        section#more-info
          h3 More Information
          p.
            The program that typesets your #[span.M \LaTeX] into math is called
            #[a(rel="external" href="http://www.mathjax.org/") MathJax], a third party
            company that uses JavaScript to communicate between the languages of #[span.M \LaTeX]
            and HTML-CSS. Basically, MathJax provides technology that allows you to display math on the
            web in an accessible, user-friendly way.
          p.
            #[a.M(rel="external" href="http://latex-project.org/intro.html") \LaTeX]
            is a language, originally developed by Leslie Lamport, used to typeset and mark up documents.
            It is a very common (perhaps the most common) system used by authors of professional math
            journals.
